columns.name: access_key_id
columns.description: The ID for this access key.

columns.name: user_name
columns.description: The name of the IAM user that the key is associated with.

columns.name: status
columns.description: The status of the access key. Active means that the key is valid for API calls; Inactive means it is not.

columns.name: create_date
columns.description: The date when the access key was created.

columns.name: access_key_last_used_date
columns.description: The date when the access key was last used.

columns.name: access_key_last_used_service
columns.description: The service last used by the access key.

columns.name: access_key_last_used_region
columns.description: The region in which the access key was last used.
